{
  "target": "MultivariateStudentT",
  "kind": "multivariate_distribution",
  "source": "Numerics/Test_Numerics/Distributions/Multivariate/Test_MultivariateStudentT.cs",
  "reference": "Test_MultivariateStudentT verified against Python scipy.stats.multivariate_t (v1.11+). CDF for dim>=2 is a deterministic K=200 stratified chi-squared(v) mixture over MultivariateNormal's CDF (no seeded state, unlike MultivariateNormal's own dim>=3 MVNDST path) -- see multivariate_student_t.hpp. Values marked 'curated via oracle_emitter --dump' were generated by running the ported logic's inputs through tools/oracle_emitter --dump against the real Numerics library and confirming them reproducible, because the corresponding C# assertion compares two runtime-computed values (a dynamically-constructed univariate StudentT.CDF, or a LogGamma expression) rather than a hardcoded literal -- there is no literal to transcribe. See fixtures/README.md.",
  "note": "GenerateRandomValues/LatinHypercubeRandomValues first-N draws are covered by the seeded_sampling case below. Skipped (not fixture-observable / not oracle values, mirrors the MultivariateNormal precedent): StratifiedRandomValues and all Test_Sampling_*/Test_LHS_*/Test_StratifiedRandomValues/Test_NonIntegerDF_LHS_Statistics/Test_InverseCDF_MarginalStatistics/Test_InverseCDF_ConsistentWithSampling KS- and moment-convergence checks (no single oracle value, just distributional-convergence checks that the first-N seeded_sampling case does not attempt to reproduce); Test_PDF_ReducesToUnivariate and Test_HighDF_ConvergesToNormal_* consistency loops (no single oracle value, just cross-checks against other distributions); all Test_ParameterValidation_*/Test_ValidateParameters_ReturnException/Test_Mahalanobis_WrongDimension/Test_InverseCDF_WrongLength exception/validation-throw tests; Test_UndefinedMoments (throws for v<=1/v<=2, exercised structurally by the port's domain_error mapping, not a value oracle); Test_Clone (Clone is not fixture-observable); Test_Constructor_DimensionOnly/Test_Constructor_LocationOnly (ctor-only property echoes, already covered by pdf_3d_at_mode's identity-scale 2-arg-ctor-equivalent construct and standard_2d's 3-arg construct); DisplayName/ShortDisplayName/Type string/enum assertions (not part of the numeric/bool fixture schema); Test_InverseCDF_Deterministic/Test_InverseCDF_TailBehavior (reproducibility/qualitative-ordering checks, no numeric oracle). IsPositiveDefinite is not independently exercised (mirrors MultivariateNormal: 'bool' mode is wired to parameters_valid() only, and both are dead-true state for any successfully-constructed instance).",
